items.name: EnvyPoodaAnimeMix
items.description:
Is this a mix? Is this trained? Maybe some of both. It's actually kind of an interesting experiment that worked out really well.

I trained a LoCon on a bunch of images I didn't like. Then I negated it (which was a much more involved process than it ought to be), and finally merged that into EnvyPoodaMix. I ended up with something that has EnvyPoodaMix's sharp lines and details, but with a more heavily anime style, and I figured it was good enough that I needed to share it. So here it is. :)

items.name: Bulma Brief (Multiple older versions LOCON) - Dragon Ball Z and Super
items.description:
I had forgotten the horror of making the first version of this LORA. I guess that's how women feel when giving birth to their second kid. Anyway. I did a retrain of my Bulma LORA, So this is one shares the same dataset as V2.

This LOCON objective is to produce as many Bulma variations as possible from Z and Super. I was unable to tag for outfits due to how stupidly large it was already. Bulma is just extremely prolific appearance wise having multiple outfits and hairstyles at different points.

Works fine with:<lyco:buruma_brief_olderV3:0.7>,buruma_brief_older, <Bulma version>

Like this: <lyco:buruma_brief_olderV3:0.7>, buruma_brief_older, buruma_dbz_buu, standing, solo, large_breasts

The available Bulma versions in this LOCON are:

  • buruma_dbz_start: Weird 80s punkish hair

  • buruma_dbz_namek: necklenght with her hairband

  • buruma_dbz_garlic: longer asymmetric hair

  • buruma_dbz_cell: A little longer than Namek and without the hairband

  • buruma_dbz_futuretimeline: Long hair

  • buruma_dbz_afro: Afro

  • buruma_dbz_buu: bobcut hair

  • buruma_super_start: Bobcut and looks older

  • buruma_super_resurrectionfreezer: similar to start but not quite

I leave to you her clothing tagging. You should be able to get the tags summary inside the dataset so experiment with that.

items.name: Orientalism Style LoRA
items.description:
This LoRA is intended to help generate images in the style of orientalism.

I recommend setting the strength to somewhere around 0.3-0.4. See uploaded images for examples. Higher strengths become more impressionistic, less coherent, and less responsive to your prompt. Don't even think about running this at full strength. I recommend the word "orientalism" in your prompt.

All example images I've uploaded are unedited outputs using the Edge of Realism checkpoint and hi-res fix.

items.name: 【再世】next life-王伟（香港演员）
items.description:
这是群星再世第三十七期，以后会不定期出去世的群星Lora，以纪念他们。

王伟，香港演员，过去三十年，我其实一直不知道他的真实姓名，但岳不群，诸葛正我，吕不韦，段王爷，完颜洪烈，吴三桂，都是他的名字，在完全没有先例经验的情况下，王伟把岳不群自宫前后各种不同的表情，神姿，仪态都表现的炉火纯青。

有人说，他演的这些角色传神的原因就是，王伟自带的贵族气质，他把书里的这些角色演活了，赐予了角色灵魂，让观众们觉得，岳不群就该像他一样阴险，吕不韦就该像他一样聪明，段王爷就该像他一样潇洒，完颜洪烈就该像他一样豁达，吴三桂就该像他一样要美人不要江山。

他不仅演出了一代宗师的清高倨傲，黑化后的阴险叵测，还演出了抛妻弃女的断情绝爱，作茧自缚的不得善终。在世人眼中，岳不群是伪君子，打着济世救人的旗号，用着下三烂的手段，做着令人不齿的勾当，其实，又有几人不是沽名钓誉。

2011年，王伟因病去世，享年72岁。

items.name: SDImageInfo
items.description:
This Windows application is capable of showing embedded info from .PNG and .JPG Stable Diffusion image files. Can be executed with filename as a parameter or image can be dragged into the application.

Supports Arrow Keys and MouseWheel to navigate between images in current directory.

Info text can be selected fully or partially and copied to clipboard (see Help).

I've created this program entirely for personal use, so no hard feelings...

Take your time to read update info. Please feel free to leave comments, error info and requests. No promises, though.

V1.1

First keyboard click swallowed - fixed.

Drag by editable fields - fixed.

Access violation error - fixed.

Cosmetic changes.

V1.2

Double-click selects all text.

Window position is saved.

V1.3

Automatically copies selected text.

V1.4

Better image resize handling.

Screen border snapping by request.

V1.5

Scroll text if amount of lines is more than visible.

Support for ComfyUI parameters (kinda) in PNG by request.

V1.6

Independent image change and text scrolling.

Refactoring and optimization.

V1.7

Software indication.

Full EXIF support (info showing after re-saved by third-party programs - if it is still there).

V1.8

Screen snapping "eased" by request.

Refactoring and optimization.

V1.9

Ctrl-Up/Down - navigate only images with SD info in current directory.

Special note. If you believe this program contains any kind of harmful code, please delete it and excuse me for trying to help you providing something useful. It's not wise to grade the program lowest value possible and shout "it's fishy", better submit info about problem you've got and receive help - helping to eliminate errors, if any.

I believe that's it for now.

items.name: Cybill Shepherd
items.description:
Cybill Shepherd is an American actress and model mainly known for her debut role in 1971's film The Last Picture Show, her role as Betsy in 1976's Taxi Driver, and for starring in the TV show Moonlighting (1985-1989) alongside Bruce Willis.

130-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (cybsheph:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: SDXL 0.9 beta tests: Famous People
items.description:
This has the same license as the 0.9 SDXL, so currently this is for research purposes!

Hello!

Since v1.0 is just around the corner, I would like to show you that training people LoRAs is very much possible.

Bear in mind, that those were tests so the quality might not be the best (also, the base is still v0.9, and v1.0 should be even better).


Samples might not be the best, I haven't used any refiners, just pure SD XL model and a LORA and nothing else.

The training dataset was of 1024x1024, so there was no upscaling (yes, freshly recut samples).

There will be still a lot of room for tweaks and improvements, you can compare it to the first dreambooths/loras. Still, as those were first tries - I'm positively surprised!

Here are three models that I was able to train during the beta. Enjoy!

I'm creating Dreambooths, LyCORIS, and LORAs. If you want to know how I do those, here is the guide: https://civitai.com/articles/7/dreambooth-lycoris-lora-guide

I upload 2-3 times a week, however, I write down suggestions all the time. If you want to see someone made into a model just leave a comment :)

Suggestions left on my donation page ( https://www.buymeacoffee.com/malcolmrey ) are taken with the highest priority and you will be able to enjoy them way before they get released here. (I accept also custom requests)

The reason is that I can't keep up with uploading and the models are being made pretty much all the time :-)

As mentioned, via the donation page I accept custom requests, so feel free to engage with me there, I will answer all your questions :)

items.name: TQ - Terraces | Ruộng bậc thang | Background LoRA
She Venom / Symbiote LoCon
items.description:
She Venom / Symbiote LoCon

LoRA request queue on my discord: https://discord.gg/DAfjhRfyEM

This model was trained using the NAI model. Trained using roughly 500 images of multiple versions of she venom. It is really good at constantly generating the pattern. Some images were male venoms, so it can generate that to some extent. You sometimes get the red spiderweb patterns on parts of it, I will try to get rid of that for the next version, which will be for SDXL.

Recommended weight is 0.8 to 1.

Trigger word is venom, if you only use that you will get the symbiote face, but since it was trained on other faces aswell you can specify what else you want and it will show a normal face.

Example images were generated using Jafamix V4 on Euler A with 30 steps and hires. fix upscaled by 1.5

I wanted this to be an update for my previous model but I couldn't make it a Lycoris so I have to make this a new upload instead.

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

items.name: TQ - Dong Thap in Vietnam | Đồng Tháp Mười | Background LoRA
Serenity
items.description:
Serenity: a photorealistic base model

Welcome to my corner!

I'm creating Dreambooths, LyCORIS, and LORAs. If you want to know how I do those, here is the guide: https://civitai.com/articles/7/dreambooth-lycoris-lora-guide

And this is my first Checkpoint Merge :-) (more details below)

I have a Buy Me A Coffee page if you want to support me ( https://www.buymeacoffee.com/malcolmrey ). You can also leave a request there if you want me to do something specific.

Here is the process of how I did it:

I was using a script from this repository: https://github.com/Faildes/Chattiori-Model-Merger

and those were the commands:

python merge.py "WS" "C:/Development/StableDiffusion/stable-diffusion-webui/models/Stable-diffusion" "photon_v1.safetensors" "realisticVisionV30_v30VAE.ckpt" --alpha 0.45 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-model-v0"
python merge.py "WS" "C:/Development/StableDiffusion/stable-diffusion-webui/models/Stable-diffusion" "juggernaut_final.safetensors" "wyvernmix_v9.safetensors" --alpha 0.45 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-model-v1"
python merge.py "WS" "C:/Development/StableDiffusion/stable-diffusion-webui/models/Stable-diffusion" "epicrealism_pureEvolutionV3.safetensors" "cyberrealistic_v31.safetensors" --alpha 0.45 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-model-v2"
python merge.py "WS" "C:/Development/StableDiffusion/stable-diffusion-webui/models/Stable-diffusion" "analogMadness_v50.safetensors" "absolutereality_v10.safetensors" --alpha 0.45 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-model-v3"
python merge.py "WS" "C:/Development/StableDiffusion/stable-diffusion-webui/models/Stable-diffusion" "icbinpICantBelieveIts_final.safetensors" "madvision_v40.safetensors" --alpha 0.45 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-model-v4"
python merge.py "WS" "C:/Development/StableDiffusion/stable-diffusion-webui/models/Stable-diffusion" "perfection_v30Pruned.safetensors" "DriveE/civitai3/huns_v10.safetensors" --alpha 0.45 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-model-v5"
python merge.py "WS" "C:/Development/StableDiffusion/stable-diffusion-webui/models/Stable-diffusion" "DriveE/civitai3/metagodRealRealism_v10.safetensors" "DriveE/civitai3/unrealityV20_v20.safetensors" --alpha 0.45 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-model-v6"
python merge.py "WS" "C:/Development/StableDiffusion/stable-diffusion-webui/models/Stable-diffusion" "DriveE/civitai3/succubusmix_v21.safetensors" "reliberate_v10.safetensors" --alpha 0.45 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-model-v7"
python merge.py "WS" "C:/Development/StableDiffusion/stable-diffusion-webui/models/Stable-diffusion" "DriveE/civitai/pornvision_final.safetensors" "DriveE/civitai/edgeOfRealism_eorV20Fp16BakedVAE.safetensors" --alpha 0.45 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-model-v8"
python merge.py "ST" "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging" "merged-model-v0.safetensors" "merged-model-v1.safetensors" --model_2 "merged-model-v2.safetensors" --alpha 0.33 --beta 0.33 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-st-model-v0"
python merge.py "ST" "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging" "merged-model-v3.safetensors" "merged-model-v4.safetensors" --model_2 "merged-model-v5.safetensors" --alpha 0.33 --beta 0.33 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-st-model-v1"
python merge.py "ST" "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging" "merged-model-v0.safetensors" "merged-model-v1.safetensors" --model_2 "merged-model-v2.safetensors" --alpha 0.33 --beta 0.33 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-st-model-v0"
python merge.py "ST" "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging" "merged-st-model-v0.safetensors" "merged-st-model-v1.safetensors" --model_2 "merged-st-model-v2.safetensors" --alpha 0.33 --beta 0.33 --save_safetensor --save_half --output "D:/Development/StableDiffusion/SDModels/Models/merging/merged-st-model-final"

As you can see, first I merged 18 models using Weighted Sum, so there were 9 pairs.

Afterwards, I merged triples using Sum Twice which in turn produced 3 models that were again merged using Sum Twice to get the final product.

I've selected 18 models that are proven to work well with my LyCORIS and LoRA models. I've applied the same testing that I do to other models and I was happy with the results (not going to rank my model since I'm biased, but I was happy with the good-to-bad ratio).

Where this model shines IMHO are the eyes and mouth.

My long-term goals were (are?) to make a decent base model and then further fine-tune it on high-quality photographs of people. But with the SDXL on the horizon, I'm not sure when/if I will have time to do it (fingers crossed?) so at least I'm doing the first part - the base model as a checkpoint merge.

Some problems I have encountered:
I initially attempted to create this model using the provided images, but it didn't yield the desired results. As a result, I decided to create my own dataset, which has led to some challenges. Although the model is functional, there are some noticeable issues. For instance, since there is no existing artwork of this character, many images in the dataset feature the character holding a weapon, resulting in a significant number of generated outputs with guns. Furthermore, a majority of the images used are in 3D, making it somewhat challenging to alter the art style effectively.

I use additional tools for my generations so my images may be different from yours. If you want to know what I use, please look at my guide.

items.name: Edward G. Robinson Lora
items.description:
I'm a lora, yeah, seeeee...

Be nice, have fun.

Edward G. Robinson (born Emanuel Goldenberg; December 12, 1893 – January 26, 1973) was a Romanian-American actor of stage and screen, who was popular during Hollywood's Golden Age. He appeared in 30 Broadway plays[1] and more than 100 films during a 50-year career[2] and is best remembered for his tough-guy roles as gangsters in such films as Little Caesar and Key Largo. During his career, Robinson received the Cannes Film Festival Award for Best Actor for his performance in House of Strangers.

During the 1930s and 1940s, he was an outspoken public critic of fascism and Nazism, which were growing in strength in Europe in the years which led up to World War II. His activism included contributing over $250,000 to more than 850 organizations that were involved in war relief, along with contributions to cultural, educational and religious groups. During the 1950s, he was called to testify in front of the House Un-American Activities Committee during the Red Scare, but he was cleared of any deliberate Communist involvement when he claimed that he was "duped" by several people whom he named (including screenwriter Dalton Trumbo, according to the official Congressional record, "Communist infiltration of the Hollywood motion-picture industry").[3][4] As a result of being investigated, he found himself on Hollywood's graylist, people who were on the Hollywood blacklist maintained by the major studios, but could find work at minor film studios on what was called Poverty Row.

Robinson's roles included an insurance investigator in the film noir Double Indemnity, Dathan (the adversary of Moses) in The Ten Commandments, and his final performance in the science-fiction story Soylent Green.[5] Robinson received an Academy Honorary Award for his work in the film industry, which was awarded two months after he died in 1973. He is ranked number 24 in the American Film Institute's list of the 25 greatest male stars of Classic American cinema. Multiple film critics and media outlets have cited him as one of the best actors never to have received an Academy Award nomination.[6][7]
